snippet.textDisplay:
) Dozens of Falun Dafa (Falun Gong) practitioners gathered at the Tel Aviv old central bus station on Saturday, January 25, 2020, to wish visiting Chinese workers a happy Lunar New Year.

On Saturdays, the Old Tel Aviv central bus station usually serves as a kind of local “Chinatown” gathering spot for hundreds of foreign Chinese workers, who arrive here to buy groceries, clothing, cellular accessories, and the like.

The groups of Chinese who arrived at the station on this particular Saturday seemed, according to their responses, to have recently arrived in Israel. They marveled at the sight of signs greeting them with “Happy New Year” and the group of practitioners freely practicing the Falun Dafa exercises.

Practitioners distributed information materials in Chinese and colorful, folded paper lotus flowers with bookmarks reading “Zhen-Shan-Ren” (“Truthfulness-Compassion-Forbearance,” the principles of Falun Dafa), and greeted the Chinese workers with a smile and a “Happy New Year.”

A TV screen on-site was broadcasting videos in Chinese, telling about the beauty of Falun Dafa and its benefits, including interviews with Western practitioners from around the world.
